{
  "stem": "1918.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 52.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it all sounded logical, sort of, you know, that it is only happening to those people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Bad as it is, they will be-- we will try to take care of them because we are safe in our own homes.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Hell no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They, they brought them in, and then it was our turn.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they put them in a designated area of the ghetto, which was a small area.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The temples and the homes of the ghetto, that was kind of the ghetto area, anyhow, where Jews lived only.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were squeezed in there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, the day after Passover, they brought us in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had to carry-- carry-- we were allowed to carry 50 kilos on our backs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And two gendarmes would come to each home, and they would march the family into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The gendarme-- most vicious animals on the face of the earth.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the man-- oh, it's too painful to talk about them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and they marched us into the ghetto, and they would put-- I think in our ghetto we had like nine people in seven feet of space, or some such thing, you know?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we quickly realized that the only thing that is most important-- even more important than eating the food that we were able to bring along-- was to keep clean-- not to have lice, not to have typhus.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we cropped our hair shorter, and we were washing all the time-- there still was water-- in order not to catch-- create typhus conditions which would threaten everybody's life.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we'd spend most of our time-- at least, that's how I remember it-- cleaning and washing and that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we stayed in the ghetto, unlike in other ghettos throughout Europe, just for a few weeks.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
